    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Lines of pipe that facilitate the movement of crude and refined liquid petroleum products by pumping. Crude oil pipelines carry unprocessed petroleum to refineries, while product pipelines transport refined petroleum products such as gasoline, kerosene, jet fuel, and heating oil from refineries to the market. </Note_Text>
